    "There he was a member of the so-called Budapest Sunday Circle (Budapester Sonntagskreis) whose members included <a href=\"/antalf\">Frederick Antal</a>, <a href=\"/hausera\">Arnold Hauser</a> and <a href=\"/tolnayc\">Charles de Tolnay</a>.": [],
    "In 1922 he moved permanently to Vienna where he was an assistant at the Gem\u00e4ldegalerie of the Kunsthistorischen Museums, under the direction of the talented <a href=\"/gluckg\">Gustav Gl\u00fcck</a>.": [
